# Keeps the Docker build context (this SignalRQueueDemo.Angular/ folder) small and reproducible -- without this,
# `docker build` would upload the host's node_modules (installed for local dev, wrong/stale relative to `npm ci`
# inside the image) and any previous dist/ output to the daemon before the build even starts.
node_modules
dist
.angular

# IDE/editor and VCS metadata -- never relevant inside the image, no reason to spend context-upload time on it.
.vscode
.git
.gitignore
*.md
